reviewText: What can I say, it's a Jess Franco Film. As Most people who have seen a Jess Franc film knows, he avoids filming outright explicit sex, although he gets close at times. This one is no exception. For fans of Jess Franco, it may be worth a watch, for others, probably not. It is filled with nudity and sex ala Franco's style. It isn't as trashy as say "Barbed Wire Dolls" and seems to be a little better than that effort.

reviewText: "Cecilia" is great in concept. It features a metric ton of full-frontal (and rear) female nudity and lots of sex. The icing on the cake is that it is beautifully-shot, with some of the best cinematography and framing of any movie that you'll see at any budget.But the problem here is that the lead character is not very attractive, and the sex, while thematically-unrestrained, is actually quite tame when it comes down to it. Lots of caressing and light touching but nothing that actually appears to be sex. And in fact even the kissing is demure.For a movie that's about sex, which "Cecilia" is, I'd expect more sexiness. The great camerawork and frequent nude scenes  are all that keeps this from a two-star rating.
